    inland config defaults: fix notebook KeyErrors at runtime-load chokepoint
    
    Inland notebooks (greensboro/austin) read optional config keys by bracket
    subscript that the coastal reference never exercises. Centralize the same
    defaults the rest of wflow_runs/sfincs_runs already apply via .get():
    
    - sfincs_runs/config.py:load_runtime now applies _apply_inland_runtime_defaults:
      static_sources_with_defaults (bbox + wflow_collection_extent) plus
      sfincs_domain_set.{domain_manifest,event_catalog_scope,evaluation_merge} and
      wflow.{domain_set_manifest,domain_set.event_catalog_scope}. Only fills keys
      inside sections the location already declares, so coastal stays coastal.
    - wflow_runs/notebook.py:domain_summary converts hard subscripts to .get().
    
    Fixes KeyError 'event_catalog_scope' and 'domain_manifest' in 04a; static scan
    of all 7 inland notebooks for config[...] chains is clean after the change.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

